properties.note:
Unorg. Fed. Terr. (1816-12-11)

1816/12/11 -> 1818/12/02

Part of the Upper Peninsula of present Michigan and the extreme eastern part of present Wisconsin became unorganized federal territory when the state of Indiana was created from Indiana, Illinois, and Michigan Territories.

(U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 57 [1816], secs. 1-2/p. 289, and res. 1 [1816]/p. 399; Van Zandt, 115)
